The paper deals with the problem of multi-target tracking in videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.AI) research. The proposed approach involves using a network flow algorithm, which is a common optimization technique in computer science (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper involves using a scoring system to measure the confidence of candidates, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
